inn1.comm: starts with an outswinger but a little too wide to bother Charles
another outswinger. Charles moves across, covers the stumps, and then lets it go
gets closer to the stumps now, and Charles defends just outside off
full, on off, shaping away, defended towards mid-off
length ball, on off, swinging away again, and defended to cover after moving across to cover the line
a maiden to kick off the game. Slightly shorter than he has been so far, but still getting the ball to move away, and beats a lazyish slash
starts with an awayswinger first up, begins just outside off, and left alone

a really good delivery, pitched on a length, on middle and leg, then swinging against the angle. He has to play at it, and is squared up. However, the the pace and bounce is not stingy enough, and the edge dies soon, and travels wide of second slip
length ball outside off, driven straight to mid-off
gets this to swing in from just outside off, defended back to him
dangerous leave. Length ball, outside off, Charles moves across a little before shouldering arms. The ball holds its line, and passes about six inches to the left of the off stump
short of a length, outside off, pushed to cover
short of a length, on off, defended off the back foot

short of a length, gives him the width, Gayle leans back to cut it hard into the ground, and between point and cover-point. Despite a heavy outfield and the McCullums chasing behind this ball, they have got four. Brendon's right arm is in contact with the ball and the rope at the same time as he puts in a desperate dive. Oh hang on. They haven't called it four. I don't think this is the right call
no room now, and Gayle defends off the back foot
fuller, no off, pushed to mid-off
Bludgeoned away. Bracewell digs this in for a gentle bouncer, and Gayle opens up the front leg to smash it to midwicket. "Neither he nor the pitch has the pace to bowl this short," says Jeff Dujon
full, swinging in, half a shout for lbw, but this is headed down leg
another ball swinging in to him, the inside edge gets him off the mark
yorker, swinging in to the left-hand batsman this time
a wide down the leg side now
Boom. Length ball, into the pads, no swing, and effortlessly lofted down the ground over long-on. Six No. 1 today
full, into the pads, dragged square onto the leg side, gets a couple square of long leg
Gayle is looking to come down the wicket, and yorks himself up with this full delivery on the pads
finally one that swings away, and Gayle doesn't go after it outside off
length ball, angling in towards top of off, defended back to him
slashes at one just wide of off and just short of a length. Beaten by the away movement
short, wide, punched to cover, fumbled there, but Gayle hasn't taken a start, and they won't get a single off the misfield
wide length ball, 132ks, driven hard, wristily, but on the half-volley and straight to mid-off

No half-volleys this time. If this was a shooting competition, Charles might even have scored a perfect 10. He has been bogged down, and is about to play out a second maiden over when he blasts this length ball down the ground. It's timed superbly, but straight to mid-off, and Williamson makes no mistake

a wicket-maiden for Bracewell as Smith flirts with this maiden. Short of a length, outside off, no intent from Smith, just the instinctive chase. Even if he had middled this, he wouldn't have got a run. Beaten
full and straight, defended back to him
this one swings away, starts just outside off, and is left alone. Good carry even though this is bowled at 131ks. Collected in front of the face by Latham
that starts a touch too wide, and swings away for Richard Illingworth to call it a wide
full, on off, angling in, bunted wide of mid-on for an easy single

Huge shout. Did the bounce save him? Ross Taylot wanted to ask Boult if he wanted a review, but Boult was quickly back to his mark. Short of a length, straightening a little, hitting the knee roll. Immediate no from Illingworth. Replays show it pitching outside leg. Just about
swiinging in towards off, defended to leg
this one kicks at him, and his head goes back a little as he defends this in front of off

And immediately he has got an lbw decision. After long deliberation, Gayle reviews it. Lovely first delivery from Southee. What a bowling change too. This is a length ball that swings in a little to hit him in front of leg. Umpire Nero has no doubt this is out. Gayle knows he hasn't hit it, he is banking on the ball pitching outside leg when he challenges this call. Replays show it pitched just in. On your bike, Chris
short of a length, outside off, left alone
digs this in, gets good bounce, neck high, left alone outside off
sharp and short, at 137ks, Samuels doesn't want to play at it, and drops his wrists. The ball nips back in to surprise him and hit his forearm
full and straight, flicked away past midwicket for one

what a bowling change this has been. Southee is on absolute fire. He might even be bowling himself into the Test XI here. Slightly short of a length, just outside off, Smith covers the angle, but this ball leaves him a little, enough to take the edge

Nearly another wicket. Swinging in again, and lobbed back down the ground, just wide of Boult. Williamson from mid-on tries to catch the non-striker backing up, and N McCullum coming in to take the throw dives into the stumps
full and swinging in, Samuels a little early into the shot again. And it lobs into the leg side again
and this time he angles it away outside off, and is left alone
swinging in a little but from too far outside off to make him play
short of a length, on off, then seams away, almost like a cutter. Beaten

the leg-side trap nearly works. Full, swinging in, middle and leg, Samuels has the instinctive flick at it. In the air she goes, just over the short midwicket, and just short  of the regulation man. Another maiden over
Southee lets him have one yorker. He knows Bravo's big back lift. Bravo keeps it out
short of a length, outside off, moving away a little, left alone
lovely outswinger. Just short of being a half-volley, and in front of off. Defended in front of his body
gives him the one angling in, turned away to square leg from in front of middle and leg
outswinger now, and not anywhere close to a half-volley. Defended from the crease
outswinger again, but a little wide, and is left alone
length ball, on off, seams away, Samuels does well to play it with soft hands and guide it past the lone slip
short, angling away, Bravo looks to cut, gets a bottom edge
left alone outside off, chest-high collection for Latham
called wide outside off. Didn't seem that wide to me. That's extremely harsh. Bravo left it alone, but it passed well inside that white guide line
another wide, and although this was wider than the previous one, I am not sure this should have been called either
fuller, on off, shaping back, defended
the inswinger now, but too full and straight, and is clipped away square on the on side
short of a length, just outside off, dabbed down to third man
leading edge as Bravo looks to whip this through midwicket. Safe to the left of Southee it goes
short of a lenght outside off, holding its line, left alone
nicely pulled away. Picks the short ball early, rocks back early, and pulls it over square leg. Takes from in front of his chest
length ball, just outside off, defended to cover
fuller, angling in towards off, solidly behind it
Trademark Bravo. Southee goes wide of the crease, bowls too full, and too straight. Bravo flicks this over midwicket. A whip really
length ball, on off, angling away, deftly guided to third man for a single
short of a length, pitched outside leg, angling towards off, pushed to leg
length ball outside off, doesn't play at it
short of a length, wide, cut away with the typical Bravo flourish. Gets a single
definite moisture there as this one kicks off a length, and Samuels has to take the bottom hand off to keep this down
short of a length, middle and leg, worked away for an easy single
driven nicely, on the bounce to cover
short of a length, left alone outside off, and boy does that climb? Collected overhead by Latham
fuller, on a length, angling in, defended off the front foot
bouncer, doesn't rise too high, but goes over the top of the stumps, and Samuels sways out of the line
wide of the crease, but too full and too straight, and he is flicked away for a single
length ball, on off, straightening, defended towards mid-on
length ball, on off, slight holding of its line, guided behind square for one
short of a length, outside off, left alone
full, really full, a half-volley really, driven wide of extra cover, and the heavy outfield keeps it in
another delivery that kicks from just short of a length. Bravo keeps it down, though, as he defends it to point
length ball, on off, defended off the back foot

Dropped. A sitter by international standards. It's Taylor again, who might have injured his left shoulder again, which he originally injured while dropping a catch in the US. Just short of a length, outside off, holds its line, takes the edge as Bravo covers the angle, and it goes about knee high to Taylor's left at first slip. He spills it, has two more stabs at it, but can't keep it in. Comes up with the hand clutching the shoulder
nicely steered away to third man as this is pitched well outside off

Oh Bravo says, you have dropped it, no worries, here I'll try to get myself out again. Premeditated big pull. And this is only just short of a lenght, and he ends up skying it. Just about clears mid-on
short of a length, outside off, left alone

nicely played. Short, outside off, Samuels plays his percentages, and goes with the upper-cut in front of square. Even a mis-hit would have gone safe here. But he has middle this for four even as both his feet are in air as he plays the shot
driven, but straight to short cover
short of a length, angling in, punched to short cover
length ball, on off, defended to leg
short of a length, outside off, a little extra bounce as he defends to cover

that's straight from a boxing match. Jabs at his throat from just short of a length, and Bravo's both feet are in the air, and the ball hits the top hand on the handle. Falls safe towards absent gully
length ball outside off, defended
short of a length, outside off, played with feet in the air again, placed wide of point for one
length ball outside off, he has left it alone... wait, not quite. Decides to have a late jab at it, and is beaten
short of a length, into the body, punched wide of mid-on for one
nicely played. This one gets big from just short of a length, but Samuels plays it late, Samuels place it with soft hands. Guides it wide of slip and wide of third man
too short this time, and this time Samuels shows some power as he punches it in front of square, wide of short cover. Lovely one-two from Samuels
that's a little wild. Trying to drag this short delivery from outside off, and gets a thick edge to third man
full, on the pads, whipped away to deep midwicket
full, swinging away slightly, driven nicely, but straight to short cover

Bravo has succeeded in getting himself out. This is the second time he has tried it. He waits as they check the no-ball, but Oram's foot is well behind as he lands. Short of a length, but Bravo's mind is made up he is going to play that extravagant whip over midwicket that is trademark Bravo. However, the length is not there, and he ends up skying it over mid-on. Enough time for Boult to run back and take it over his shoulder. That ball was closer to a pulling length than driving length
nearly another, but you have to give credit to Samuels's soft hands. Short of a length, holding its line, but edged short of the only slip
extra bounce again, from just short of a length, defended with the bottom hand off
short of a length, outside off, left alone
short of a length, outside off, squared up as he defends it
defended with an open face, towards gully - a wicket-maiden for Oram. He is using his height superbly here
short of a length, Pollard plays for the angle, but the ball leaves him a little. Beaten
short of a length again, but well outside off, and left alone
Nearly played on. Actually nearly left on. Length ball outside off, he decides late to leave it alone, and the ball hits the inside edge of the retreating bat. Misses the stumps by inches
short of a length, wide, punched away to sweeper-cover. Samuels looking in good touch now
short of a length, outside off, drops his wrists as he doesn't make an attempt to play at it
goes wide of the crease, angling in towards the top of off, defended from the crease
another spitting delivery as Samuels has to take his bottom hand off and the ball still hits the handle. Kicked from just short of a length
stays back to defend this short-of-a-length delivery outside off
slightly fuller, Samuels is back, and the ball hits the sticker on the bat as he defends
short of a length, angling in, tucking him up, defended
wider of the crease, angling in, nicely tucked away wide of midwicket for one
length ball outside off, Pollard well forward to defend
gets turn first ball, and is wided down the leg side
the other one, the arm ball, pitched outside leg, and hits him in front of leg
short of a length, makes room to punch him, but straight to cover
short of a length, pulled away fine for one
arm ball, pitches leg, angling towards off, defended off the front foot
flighted outside off, driven to long-off for one
length ball, on off, Samuels drops and runs, and Pollard responds. Easy single to cover
short of a length, steered over gully for one
drop and run again. This is going straight to mid-on, but Pollard's big strides make a mockery of this tight single
short, angling in, steered wide of gully this time
length ball, angling in, left alone
wide of the crease, short of a length, angling into the pads, pushed to square leg
wide of the crease again, and digs this time, and gets it to rise chest-high. However, it is wide outside off, and Pollard is not inconvenienced in staying away from this delivery
length ball, middle and leg, defended to leg
short, but quick, at 94ks, and he beats him on the pull with his pace
tossed up, turning into the pads, inside edge onto the pad, and then wide of the keeper
short, turning down leg, and Latham can't get a touch to it
length ball, on off, thick edge, gets him a single
top shot. Length ball, flat, on off, he goes inside-out, and clears mid-off with a flat hit with ease
flighted on off, defended solidly
short of a length, outside off, defended to mid-off
length ball, angling in towards off, defended to mid-on
walks down the wicket, yorks himself up, digs this out to mid-on, and steals a single. Ridiculous how Pollard finishes this short singles without any trouble at all
short of a length, outside off, defended with an open face
slashed away, but safe. Goes wide of the crease, but bowls short, and Samuels goes after it. Not entirely in control of it, but wide enough of gully. Calculate shot again
short of a length, outside off, defended square on the off side
length ball, on the pads, but played straight to square leg
flighted outside off, driven down to long-off for one
short of a length, outside off, defended off the back foot
full, really full, gets an inside edge and drives it into his boot
short, outside leg, pulled to long leg
flighted outside off, no turn on it, takes the leading edge as Pollard looks to turn this to leg. Safely it goes, between cover and extra cover
length ball, no movement, defended off the front foot
short, outside off, and he chases it late. A buzz goes around the ground. They don't approve of this waft. Beaten
short of a length, just outside off, defended
lenght ball, into the pads, worked away for a single
short, outside off, left alone
short of a length, outside off, rocks back to cut, but finds cover-point
flighted outside off, takes a thick edge as Pollard goes for a big drive. Gets it fine of short third
short, turning down leg, another wide
short, punched to deep midwicket
quick and straight, defended off the front foot
Lovely shot. Samuels just takes half a stride down the wicket to turn this into a half-volley, and lofts him over long-on. Samuels is looking really good here
short and turning down again
uses his feet again. Down the wicket to turn this into a half-volley, and drills this back past him. There is a long-on in place, but he has no chance

N Mac strikes back. Samuels can't review this. Not that that would have made too much of a difference. Short of a length, pitches middle and leg, skids through, stays slightly low, and turns back in a little to trap him plumb. A good hand from Samuels, but the look on his face said he had done only half the job so far
length ball, outside off, defended off the front foot
digs this in short, 134ks, over the top of the stumps, but Pollard does well to drop the wrists and sway out of its line

they have called this a no-ball for being the second bouncer in the over, although I didn't see the signal for one in the over. Must have missed it. That's a sharp bouncer, Pollard gets inside the line, ducks a little. And after his ducking this goes head high. In his normal stance, there is now way this was over the shoulder
short of a length, wide, goes after it, and is beaten by the lack of bounce
yorker length, dug into the leg side for one
wafts at a wide delivery with no foot movement. Beaten comfortably, although there is a half shout for a catch at the wicket
short of a length, outside off, guided past slip for one
length ball, into the pads, pushed to short midwicket
short this time, punched uppishly, just short of short midwicket
length ball on off, defended back to him
pushed through outside off, defended with an open face
slows it down a little, 83ks, tossed up outside off, defended
plays a forward-defensive, gets an inside edge onto the pad, but there is no bat-pad in place
swinging into the pads, starts too straight, but Pollard misses out and gets a leg-bye
short, outside off, cuts, gets a bottom edge that falls short of slip
short of a length, just outside off, defended off the back foot
length ball, angling in, defended in front of off
short of a length, angling in, defended to leg
moves insode the line as this angles in, and clips it away towards deep square leg
length ball, turning into the pads, padded away
flighted outside off, driven to long-on for the first run off Nicol
turning into the pads, turned away to square leg, B Mac tries to catch Pollard backing up, misses, but they don't take the overthrow
played with the tun, straight to short straight midwicket
short, puled square, but B Mac is alert at square leg
flighted, middle and leg, defended back to him
appeal for a catch down the leg side, but that's more to make sure the umpire knows it has come off the batsman's person. It's the pad this time

Are they going to review it? No, New Zealand aren't. Short of a length, outside off, nips back in a little, and goes through the gap between bat and pad. There is a noise, but Illingworth rules not out. Replays prove him correct. Could have flicked the back thigh on the way through. Top decisions
angling away outside off, left alone
beats the inside edge on his bat with a delivery angled in. Hit in front of stumps but too high
short of a length, outside off, 136ks, left alone, collected in front of the face by Latham
full, into the pads, angling too far, concedes too leg-byes, but adds to maidens tally
Thomas finally gets a run off Nicol. Worked wide of square leg
flighted outside off, defended back to him
short of a length, goes back to punch him down to long-off
short of a length, turning in, beaten by the turn as he looks to work this to leg
short of a length, quick to rock back and pull it through midwicket
flighted, turning into leg, worked to square leg

Missile from Pollard. That looked like he was gone for all money as it left the bat. Flat hit, no height on it, and the long-on is back, but it is hit so fast that N McCullum doesn't have time to take the couple of steps to his right that would take him to the ball. Pollard's first boundary - would you believe it?
angled a bit too wide, and left alone
drops this lenght ball to wide of midwicket for a single
length ball, dabbed to the left of point but B McCullum is superb there
short of a length, outside off, punched to cover-point
tucked away off the hip for a single
length ball, on the pads, worked away for an easy single
full, middle and leg, worked away for a single
lenght ball, middle and leg, defended
short of a length, punched straight to short straight midwicket
short of a length, dabbed away for a single past point
short of a length, outside off, punched away, but straight to cover
full, driven to long-on for one
short of a length, swipes at the first ball, and connects well to swat it past square leg for four
full, flicked away, can't beat midwicket
short of a length, outside off, runs it down to third man for one
full and straight, and he plays across the line, and misses. The inside edge saves him, though
that doesn't matter to Pollard. He gets a length ball, stands tall, and swipes it between long-on and deep midwicket. Not a fielder moved
full, near yorker, gets a single to long-on
short, wide, punched straight to extra cover
turning into the pads, helped around the corner
flighted on middle and leg, and defended to midwicket
full and straight, driven down to long-on for one
slog-swept into the breeze for a six. These boundaries are not big enough if he connects. He has taken this from outside off, and has hit pretty flat and over deep midwicket
short, and he has pulled it along the ground to deep midwicket
wide of the crease, full outside off, dragged to long-on for one
full, into the pads, and he has flicked it almost Dwayne Bravo-style to pick four runs wide of midwicket
short of a length, outside off, pushed to cover
cut away, but Williamson dives to his left at point to save three runs
wide yorker from wide of the crease, toe-ends it to short fine leg for one
slower ball, one a length, pushed towards midwicket for one
length ball, outside off, Thomas goes for the drive, slices it over cover. Safe shot
short, pulled away with the front leg in air, looks like Bravo again, and gets a couple past square leg
length ball, on off chipped over his head for a single
yorker from slightly wide of the crease, kept out for a single
wide length ball, Thomas goes after it, gets a healthy edge through the vacant slip region for four
fuller, half-volley eve, and Thomas has creamed this drive between cover and extra cover. Thomas is sure making up for that slow start
wide of the crease, bowls a wide yorker, slightly too wide, and called
wide yorker again, this time Pollard plays at it, and hits it straight to point
slightly short of being a yorker, hit to extra cover for a single. He was well in even if Oram had hit
full and wide again, gets a single to extra cover to reach his personal best in ODIs
goes for the wide yorker again, ends up bowling a full toss, which Pollard drags into the leg side for four, between square leg and midwicket
wide yorker gone wrong again. It;s a now a full wide delivery,and he has driven it past extra cover. Brings up a mature fifty for Pollard. One of his best efforts
goes for the yorker at the stumps this time, beats the inside edge and ekes out a dot ball
Thomas has sent this out f the ground. Jumps out of the crease, makes a bit of room to swing his arms, and lofts this length ball over long-off
short of a length, outside off, dabbed away for a single
flat, into the pads, pushed to long-on for one

soft dismissal. Low full toss, Thomas has the right idea, looking to chip it cover cover who is in at a short position, but Thomas hits this straight to that man. Anyway, Thomas has done his job. over to Sammy and Russell
flighted outside off, defended off the front foot
shorter, turning down leg for a wide
length ball, on off, pushed back to Nicol
full, on off, drilled to long-on, threatening to burst through the hands of N Mac there, but he does well to keep it in
short of a length, dabbed to point, where B Mac is in from the circle to cut the single
nonchalantly pulled away. That's a long hop at 131ks, and he pulls this square from just outside off
short of a length, punched straight to short cover
length all, angling in, inside edge onto the pad gets him a single
low full toss, drilled back over his head, but long-off is straight enough to come around and cut it off
short of a length, on off, steals a single to point
and he pushes this wide of cover for a single
sees him make room, follows him with a yorker, which is dug out for a single
length ball, whipped away to long-on for one

the only loose shot from Pollard perhaps. Well bowled too. Slower-ball bouncer, Pollard makes room, his head falls away as he swings at this, and gets a top edge that is taken comfortably at point. Important innings from Pollard. Mature one too
length ball, on off, defended to cover
short of a length, run down to third man for one
short, wide, but cut away straight to point
length ball, Sammy's eye light up, but this one holds its line and beats the almighty swing of the bat
short and wide, and even Sammy can't reach it
goes after another length delivery, gets a thick edge that drops just short of third man
Dropped. Russell has hardly had his eye in, that's why he has mis-hit this pull. Looks like an easy enough chance at long-off, but while going back Southee tripsover, loses his footing, and the ball
length ball, outside off, driven to long-off for one
full and straight, drilled to long-off for one
short to Russell. There seems to be some sort of plan to Russell to bowl short. Dabbed away for a single
slower ball gone wrong, wide down leg
slower ball again, Sammy checks his big shot, takes a single to long-on
yorker, on leg stump, can't do anything with it
length ball, outside off, gets a single to point
misses out on a leg-side full toss, is hit on the pad
full and wide, driven nicely, but Taylor dives to his right at short straight cover to deny them a single
low full toss, dragged form outside off for a single to midwicket
full, outside off, dug out for a single to deep cover
lovely hit. Short of being a yorker, and he goes on a knee, and drives this over extra cover. Holds the pose too
low full toss, and finds midwicket again - that's quite a few full tosses gone unpunished
low full toss outside off, hit to midwicket again
angling into the pads, short too, Sammy plays an effective little pick-up shot to help it over long leg

dropped by Oram, back-to-back sixes for Sammy. It's a little harsh to call this a drop, but we have been ruined for the unspectacular by some extraordinary fielding nowadays. Full, hit flat and to the left of long-off, Oram makes ground, has both feet in the air when he makes contact with the ball, but the ball bursts through. Could never have been sure if he would have stayed inside
full and straight, driven wide of long-on for two

full again, driven wide of long-on for twohe has found long-on with this low full toss. Timed really well. It's that half-cock punch that he plays that travels miles. But this time he has failed to get any elevation, and has picked Guptill out at long-on
length ball outside off, holds its line, beats the defensive bat
length again, pushed to extra cover for one
lenght ball, angling across, guided to third man for one
full and straight, driven to long-off for one
length to Narine, and he dabs it to point for a single
yorker gone wrong. A comfortable full toss on the pads, and he has heaved it over midwicket for an easy six
slower short ball, and he has picked it early, and clubbed it down the ground for a huge straight six. That seems like it has touched the sky before landing in the stands
full and straight, dug out for a single
full and straight, dug out for another single
length ball outside off, he slogs, gets an edge, gets the single to third man

slower ball, called wide down the leg side, Oram says it has hit something on the way. Big Jake says he wants to review it, but of course you can use reviews only for dismissals. Seems to have come off the glove, and bounced in front of the keeper
length ball, drilled down the ground, and Guptill, eager to keep them down to one, lets it slip through for four

drilled towards Guptill at long-on again, but this time in the air, and despite the swerve away from him, Guptill takes the catch. Had he missed that, it could have been worth 20 runs in the final equation
another wide - 20 runs off wides now
o boy, an immaculate forward-defensive from Best, back to the bowler
steers this down to third man for a single
full, middle and leg, driven to long-on for one
full, on off, played with an open face, gets a single
full toss, mis-hit down towards long-on
full, on off, driven inside-out to long-off for a single
WI are bowled out. Best goes for the big slog sweep, and is cleaned up by a leg-stump yorker

inn2.comm: short of a length, into the body, pushed to midwicket

that's edged for six. Best digs this in short, provides him the width, half-deliberate, half-top-edged over third man, where for some reason  Russell was a fair way in from the boundary. That's on a 60-metre field
ticked into the body, concedes a leg-bye
short of a length, outside off, left alone
wide down the leg side
full, outside off, 147ks, left alone

full, straight, beaten for the pace, and Best has got his wicket. he is down on his knees, looking skyward with arm aloft. What a celebration. Guptill has contributed to the dismissal by playing across the line to a full delivery headed for middle stump. He is a goner as soon as he misses it, but he has also been done in for pace a little
short of a length, outside off, dabbed away for a single
short of a length, stump to stump, defended
length ball, shaping away from outside off, left alone
bowled from behind the stumps, on a length, in front of off, defended to cover

misses all around. Russell misses his line and bowls well down the leg side, McCullum misses on the glance, and is hit on the pad, and while the deflection hasn't gone too wide, Thomas has dived over the ball to concede four leg-byes
length ball outside off, pushed to cover
digs this in, gets it to rise towards the splice of the bat, fended into the leg side - bowled at 146ks
short, wide, doesn't rise much, beats him on the cut
short of a length, 145.2ks, again hits the sticker on the bat as Nicol defends
length ball, kicks at him again, off the splice it goes towards square leg, and McCullum is deceptively quick in completing that quick single
this is pitched in his own half, McCullum on his toes to defend, right behind it
full and fast, 148.1ks, on off, driven to mid-off. Half shout for lbw with bat and pad together, but there is a lot of bat involved in this, and seemingly before the pad
Nicol has been facing Best in high140s, and when he gets Russell at 131ks, he dances down the track, and despite the swing, he lofts a length ball over mid-off
short of a length, outside off, steered square of third man for a couple
short, wide, 131.5ks, and Nicol goes for the cut in font of square, and over the top. No risk involved
short of a length, into the body, tucked away for a single
length ball, on off, and he hustles through a single to mid-off
short, outside off, looks to pull this, gets a bottom edge, far enough off the stumps
dangerous shot, across the line to a full and straight and fast delivery, bowled at 148.3ks. Gets the bat down in time, takes a single to square leg
short, into the body, and now at 149.1ks, and clearly beats him for the pace, although he concedes a leg-bye
short of a length, angling in, 147.2ks, clipped away for a single
done in for pace again. Short of a length, angling in towards off, McCullum looks for the punch, gets a thick inside edge for four
another inside edge as McCullum looks to punch. This time it goes straight to square leg
wide down the leg side, Best goes "catch it, catch it". Thomas is untidy again down leg, and allows an extra run

Nicol is playing a neat little gem here. He has this liking for a shimmy down to quicks. Just half a stride down, takes this on the half-volley, and flicks him clean over long-on. Already two sixes for Nicol
short of a length, on the stumps, punched to mid-on
length ball, angling in, pushed to short midwicket
short of a length, outside off, punched to cover

that's a manufactured shot. Goes back to punch a length ball between cover-point and point. Pollard chases, slides and saves, giving them enough time to take a rare three at this ground. Only the 14th three in fact, as opposed to 133 sixes
short of a length, outside off, punched to mid-off
bouncer, over the top of the stumps, ducks under it
short of a length, into the body, worked past short fine line for one
and it goes through where the first slip would have been. Short of a length, Nicol goes hard at it, gets an edge, and will take the four
short of a length, angling in, Nicol is forward and in defence
stays on that nagging length, just outside off, and Nicol defends
short of a length, outside off, punched to cover
short of a length. angling in, defended towards mid-on
short of a length, angling in towards off, pushed to cover

soft dismissal. There have been quite a few in this series. Slightly short of a lenght, and he goes to pull it, picking the short midwicket with surgical precision. Not the length to pull. And he is not pleased with himself. The PA system at the ground plays, "Hit the road Jack... and don't you come back no more."
short of a length, on off, defended back to him
bowls this short, just outside off, extra bounce, and Taylor doesn't play at it
hands on heads as Taylor cuts this in the air. Not much width, but he goes after it, and hits it uppishly, but well wide of point
fuller, on off, and he has off-driven this between the bowler and mid-off who is a little wide. Just walked into this push-drive
Sammy stays short of a length, in line with off, and draws another dot
slightly fuller, pushed off the front foot, takes the quick single, has to run around Sammy, but the throw from Samuels is well wide
length ball, wide, 128ks, driven to point
length ball, on off, no movement, but no room either. Defended
short of a length, outside off, cut away to third man for one
full, outside off, driven wide of mid-off for a single
starts with an offbreak, Nicol is already down a knee to sweep. Played to short fine
goes down for the sweep again, beaten by the turn
this one turns down the leg side
the straighter one, but Nicol is sweeping regardless, and gets a single to fine leg
another straighter one, Taylor moves across, plays this from off, into the leg side
flighted outside off, not much time for the ball to turn, defended off the front foot
another straight one, Taylor stays back to defend it outside off
length ball, on off, pushed to point, Smith misfields, but they decide against a single
length ball outside off, no movement, driven to cover

Nicol has had a brain freeze. Sammy has picked up a wicket after coming on to bowl when the heat was on. He goes across the line to play the pick-up shot, but the length - much like Bravo earlier in the day - is a little too short for a front-foot shot. As a result he gets a bit too under it, and finds deep midwicket
short of a length, on off, bunted into the leg side, between the two deep fielders, gets a couple
fuller, on off, defended off the front foot
wide length ball, Taylor walks into the drive, and places it wide of extra cover. Lovely drive again
and he is not picking him. Tossed up outside off, the straighter one, and he is searching for the offbreak. Beaten
short, pulled away for a single
quick offbreak, sliding through, beats the inside edge, but is headed down leg
moves across the line to pull this to deep square leg
flighted outside off, defended solidly
short of a length, turning in, pushed to square leg
short, outside off, dragged to deep square for a single
nicely played. Short of a length, outside off, opens the face late, guides it past slip, but Russell at third man puts in a good foot around to save two runs
short of a length, angling in, defended off the back foot
length ball, angling in towards off, defended
length ball, on off, no room, defended back to him
short of a length, angling in towards middle, pushed to leg
into the pads, worked away for a single
straighter one again, but too full to bother him, as he defends it
short of a length, turning in, pushed to square leg

he is gone. Williamson has had a horrid time of it with Narine. He is reviewing this lbw decision, though. Quicker, straighter delivery, no thumb sticking out as Narine goes up for the delivery. Short of a length, but skiddy, and beats Williamson on the pull, which is not quite one. Pitched outside off, hits him in front of off, and that's a review exhausted
tossed up outside off, left alone
offbreak, pitches off, left alone
length ball, on off, pushed to mid-on
short of a length, on off, pushed back to him
fuller, angling in, pushed to short straight midwicket
short of a length, accurate, defended to cover
short of a length again, but provides him width, which he uses to run it down to third man
wafts at a wide delivery without any foot movement, and is beaten. A nervous shot. He wouldn't have managed even a single even if he had middled it
turning into the pads, defended back
turning into the pads again, but finds midwicket this time
defended off the back foot as he flattens the trajectory
the straighter one, defended off the back foot
into the pads this time, misses out, hit on the pad
tossed up outside off, defended to finish the maiden over of the innings
short of a length, on off, defended
length ball, on off, defended to leg
length ball, angling in, defended to leg
short of a length, outside off, wants a quick single as he dabs it to point, but is sent back, and rightly so

Had Bravo been right at the rope, Taylor was gone. He has pulled this, and on this small field, he has managed to lob the boundary fielder, and then get it to bounce inside. I have no clue why fielders come in so far on 60m boundaries
short of a length, pushed down to long-on for one
full, on off, driven to long-off for one
flighted on off, defended back to him
short of a length, goes back to punch him wide of point for a single
straighter one, on a length, on off, Taylor defends it back
tossed up outside off, assured that he can get outside the line, Taylor goes for a sweep, but finds the short fine leg
offbreak, tossed up high, outside off, beats the bat, hits the pad, but is turning too much to get an lbw verdict
length ball, outside off, allowed to go through
length ball outside off, and left alone again
full, just outside off, jammed out to point
full and slightly wide again, jammed out to point again
short of a length, pushed to mid-off
short of a length, on the stumps, defended to pay out a maiden
turning into the pads, worked past midwicket for one
tries the big sweep, premeditated, beaten outside off
quicker straighter one, full outside off, and left alone
offbreak, short of a length, punched to point
length ball, middle and off, stays back to defend
looks to paddle, doesn't pick the other one, the ball comes back and hits the pad, but outside the line, hence not given out
length ball, on off, no room, defended to mid-on

fuller, pushed to Pollard at short straight midwicket. Pollard fumbles, and the two batsmen are loitering around wondering if they should take a single. Suddenly they realise Pollard has the ball again, and Taylor has to rush back. Third umpire finds out he is back in
short of a length, angling in, worked away for a single
digs this in short, just outside off, left alone
dug in short again, just outside off, and Latham doesn't play at it - he is 2 off 19 now
full, just outside off, pushed to extra cover
short of a length, on off, worked wide of Gayle at midwicket for one
premeditated lap shot fine of fine leg for a couple. They try to go at Taylor's end who is taking it easy, but Samuels is no position to take the wide throw
another paddle, this time off a full toss, and straight to the fielder at fine leg
powerful sweep, gets a single to deep square
short of a length, on off, gets a thick edge to point
full, middle and leg, driven to long-on for one
full, on the pads, pushed to midwicket
wide low full toss, Latham reaches out for it, and steers it fine of point and wide of third man
short of a length, angling towards off, pushed wide of point
short of a length, outside off, played off the front foot, towards cover
wide half-volley, Taylor square-drives, but finds Smith at point. Six feet either side, and he would have got four
full outside off, driven to cover, on the bounce
length ball, pitched outside leg, hits the pad
fired in flat again, yorks him up inn front of leg
darted away again, just outside of,f he cuts, and finds Best at point
yorker again, dug out, but another doubt. Pressure building up
slightly slower through the air, defended in front of off
gets width, guides this past point, comes back for two - takes him to 13 off 33
short of a length, outside off, pushed to point
rapid. Short, 144ks, looks like Taylor might get four with a cut, but the extra bounce means he has to abort the shot, and drop his wrists out of the way
full and straight, hit back to him, and Best has a mock-throw at Taylor. The crowd likes it
dug in short again, rising towards the chest, fended down
short of a length, headed for top of off, defended solidly
sucker ball after a testing over full of short bowling. Thrown up full and wide, 143ks, Taylor goes for the drive, and is beaten. Very nearly the perfect over. Maiden nonetheless
full, on leg, Latham thinks he has got a single to long-on, but Samuels fields to his left
driven up to long-off for one

Taylor is trying to drag this into one of his famous slogs, Samuels fires this in. Hits the toe of the bat, into the boot, into the pad, and then to the keeper, who flicks the bail. Taylor is back, though. They are still going to the third umpire. They could even be checking for the catch here. Not a catch either. It hits the ground before hitting the boot
short of a length, punched down the ground for one
short of a length, on off, punched square, but finds point
fuller, on leg, worked past midwicket for a single
sharp bouncer to Latham too. Straight, over the top of the stumps, chin-high, beats the upper-cut, at 146ks
length ball, 147ks, but too wide outside off
short of a length, 146ks, tucks him up, on middle and leg, pushed back to Best
length ball, on off, 145ks, pushed to cover
misses his line but minimum damage down as Latham clips him off the pads for a single to fine leg
short of a length, on off, defended off the back foot

more ordinary work from Thomas followed by ordinariness from Russell. Short outside off, stays low, reaches Thomas on half-volley, but he lets it through, and then Russell from third man only sticks out a boot in vain
flighted on middle and leg, defended
tries the slog sweep, beaten outside off
full, on off, driven to long-off for one
darted into the pads, helped away past short fine leg for two
short of a length, on off, defended back to Samuels
surprised by the full toss, bowled at 116ks, almost the Sammy pace, and he hits it straight to midwicket
short outside off, he reaches for it to cut it for a single to deep point
full, on off, Taylor moves across for the slog, gets a thick inside edge for a couple, wide of deep square

short of a length, Taylor moves across again, bunts this into the leg side, wants two, but Thomas gives chase, Sammy goes to collect at striker's end, and Gayle at non-striker's. Good alert team work from everybody keeps them down to one
short of a length, angling away, punched away for a single
short of a length, outside off, runs it down to third man for one
angling into the pads, pushed uppishly to mid-on for a single
juicy full toss but he hits straight to deep midwicket on the bounce
Thomas appeals for bat before wicket, not for the first time today, even as Taylor gets a single off the thick outside edge
angled across, conceding a single off the bottom edge
full and fast, hit back to MS
full toss, at nelson kmph, driven to long-off for one
makes room to drive this wide of long-off for a couple
length ball, outside off, pushes on the run, and gets a single to mid-off
short, into the body, pulled away to deep square, but he has overstepped too
moves across to a length ball outside off, and swats it six feet to the left of Samuels at deep midwicket, who puts in no attempt to save the fur runs. Almost as if scared of the ball
full, outside off, pushed to point
short of a lenght, kicking up, beats the bat, but Thomas standing up concedes a bye
dug in short, pulled away for a single to deep square
short of a length, outside off, punched to long-on for one
full, on off, driven to long-on for one
driven to short straight extra where Gayle dives but only manages to deflect it to long-off
turning into the pad,s helped around the corner for one
fired into the pads, helped away for a single
full, middle and off, pushed back to Samuels
low full toss, driven down to long-on for one
slower ball, flicked away into the on side for one
short of a length, outside off, holds its line, beats his waft
full, angling in, driven to deep cover for one
short of a length, angling in, off the inside edge it goes into the on side where there is no man to save a single
length ball, starts wide, shapes away a little, called wide
quick single as he pushes this to Smith and point and responds to Taylor's call. Smith goes for the non-striker's end, Latham dives, sees the throw sail over the stumps, and takes the overthrow too
short of a length, angling in, gets a leading edge as he looks to work this to leg. Takes the single to third man
quick, gets a thick edge to point
full, on the pads, pushed to midwicket
yorker, on off, dug out straight to point

Latham has finally succumbed. Three dots in a row draw out a forceful shot to a short-of-a-length delivery just outside off. He is cramped for room, and edges it through to Thomas. This wicket ensures at least one new batsman in the Powerplay
tossed up outside off, defended after moving across
full, outside off, driven to long-on for one
short of a length, angling in, dabbed wide of point for a single
angling into the pads, fails to make connection, but takes the leg-bye
slower ball, 111ks, offcutter, cut away to point
quicker delivery, 134ks, slashes at it wide outside off, and is beaten
length ball, angling in, nudged into the on side for one
slower ball, defended to cover
full, on off, driven back to Samuels
full and fast again, driven to long-on for one
full and fast again, 113ks, clipped into the on side, McCullum turns down the second. At any rate, that brings up the fifty for Taylor
slower through the air, 95ks, driven down to long-on for a single
full toss, into the pads, pushed to long-on for one
shorter, he moves across to work this into the on side. Soft hands mean they risk the second, and Bravo's return is wide. He would have made it anyway
short of a length, into the body, dropped for a single into the leg side
short of a length again, but down the leg side. That's 19 extras vs NZ's 26
short of a length, wide, runs it down to third man for one
slower ball - his first slower ball, 113ks, short of a length, on off, pushed wide of cover for one
steered away down to third man
just short of a yorker, pushed wide of mid-on for one
stays low and beats McCullum's attempt to punch him away - 12 off the first two overs of PP
full and straight, driven down to long-on for one
gets rare width from Samuels, but he finds point with the square-drive
fast length ball, pushed back to him
low full toss now, and hit straight to midwicket
fired into the toes at 116ks, dug out to the right of Gayle at midwicket, and they steal one
beaten by pace, hit on the toe, but he still hobbles through for a leg-bye
misses out. Gets a length ball into the pads, but is late into it, and has to contend with a leg-bye
short of a length, N Mac goes across the line to tuck this into the leg side for one. On the way back Tino sticks his tongue out to N McCullum
full, outside off, gives him room to drive, not timed perfectly, but he will pick a couple past extra cover
slower ball, on a length, on off, slogged to deep square for one

Best can stick his tongue out all he want now. He has got his man. McCullum gets a rare full ball from Best who has bee peppering him with short stuff. He drives, but all he manages is to run it straight to point where Sammy accepts it gleefully
short of a length, on off, no room, 147ks, squares him up in defence
Taylor finally gets his slog working. Moves across and never mind Samuels's pace, he gets under this length ball and clears cow corner. You could name it Taylor corner too
Onto the roof. Slog-sweeps from outside off, and well over long-on. He connects them superbly when he gets down to them
fast and furious, 120ks, Taylor is late into this slog, gets a thick edge that clears point
hit straight to midwicket this time
driven straight to Pollard at mid-off but he makes it through for a comfortable single
low full toss, driven to long-off for one
short of a length, on off, pushed to long-off for one
short, Taylor's bottom hand drags it fine, but can't beat short fine leg
makes room, Russell bowls offcutter outside leg, pushed to cover
short, slight width available, the angle too, but he finds point
slower ball, 104k, full, near yorker, just outside off, played back to Russell
pushes it wide outside off, a touch too far
swings at a length ball outside off, beaten by the angle
doesn't read this offbreak, picks it off the pitch, cramped on the cut, gets a single past slip
short of a length, squares him up in defence
full, on off, driven to long-off for one
the other one, the one the breaks away, pitches outside leg, hits the pad, and goes for a leg-bye
the rare loose ball, but he has pulled it straight to long leg for one
the knuckle ball again, on a length, on off, turning away, dabbed into the off side for a single
length ball, on off, Taylor likes it. Moves across, gets under it, and without a heavy back lift, he lofts it over long-on
Taylor is dealing in braces of sixes. Again he has got successive sixes. Russell's yorker goes wrong, and he slog-sweeps this low full toss from outside off and sends it over midwicket
short of a length, stays deep inside the crease, and swats this towards deep midwicket, and charges back for the second. Into the 90s now

He is not all about the on side. Those two sixes must have really had an impact on Russell's line, who goes wide outside off when he goes full, and Taylor drives him over extra cover for four. Roscoe is turning it on
short of a length, no room, bunted towards deep midwicket with soft hands, and he comes back for an easy second
length ball, on off, driven down to long-on for a single
offbreak, starts on off, hits the pad in front of leg, goes for a leg-bye
straighter one, Oram defends from deep inside the crease
offbreak, short of a length, on leg, beats the push, and Thomas sees Oram lift his push for a brief moment, and breaks the wicket. The umpires don't go to the TV replay. They might have been right
length ball, on leg, moving towards off, defended to cover
makes room to drive this to sweeper-cover for a single
Taylor seems to be playing for the straighter one as he goes to late-cut this, but is surprised by the offbreak, and is cramped up. Another dot
short of a length, outside off, Oram doesn't get wood on leather as he wafts at it
full toss, just outside off, hit back to Best, and the crowd cheers as Best fields it to keep it down to a dot
low full toss, Oram clips it away for a single - 6 off 17 now, he needs to do better
full, outside off, driven to deep point for one

Best is looking heavenwards again. It's the good old you-miss-I-hit stuff from him. Oram, under pressure from the many dot balls he has faced, makes room, but Best remains full, straight and fast. And he hits the middle stump. Timbahhhh. An underwhelming innings from Oram, who seems to now justify N McCullum's promotion ahead of him
length ball, into the pads, worked to long leg for one
offbreak, deflected into the on side for a single
straighter one, takes it from in front of off, works it into the leg side for one
legbreak, drops it into the off side, wide of cover, for one
the straighter one again, late-cut to short third for a single to bring up his hundred. Calmly he accepts applause. His first ODI since October, and he scored a century in that game too
turning into the pads, pushed to short midwicket
the legbreak from Narine, punched away, but straight to short cover
Bravo gets away with it. Full, on the pads, swung away, but straight to long leg
wide yorker, well inside that tram line, but out of Bracewell's reach. Top delivery
full toss, hit down to long-off for one
low full toss on the pads, and he gets a single again to long leg. Solid over for West Indies so far
low full toss again, gets a single to long-off

this is a high full toss, and Taylor accepts it with glee, lofting him over square leg for his fifth six. What's more? He wants a call for a no-ball for a high full toss. Doesn't seem that high, though. The umpires tell him just that
Bracewell charges at the first ball of Narine's last. Bracewell has made a little too much room as Narine floats this wide outside off, and the mist-hit settles with long-off
offbreak, cramps him from a short of a length, punched down to long-on
legbreak, pitches on a length, in front of off, turning away, defended back to him

short delivery, Southee swings at it expecting it to turn in, but the ball turns away, and beats the edge, or so it seems. Thomas appeals, he is so confident he has convinced Sammy to review the decision. And oh my word, Narine doesn't have any part of the foot behind the line. Thomas and Sammy might have conceded a no-ball and a free hit here. Plus lose their review. I think it will be pretty generous if this is not called a no-ball. Long wait for the decision. Tension all around as players form small-small groups to chat among themselves. Not-out called, but Narine has been allowed to get away with that no-ball. How crucial could a free hit be in the context of this match? Ordinary umpiring there
full, outside off, driven to long-on for one
swept away powerfully, but only for a single. Narine finishes with 2 for 20 off his 10. What pressure he has exerted. Could me the watch-winning turn
short of a length, inside edge into the pads, drops into the off side, Taylor turns down the single. Cheers all around

Sammy takes the catch. Taylor perishes. There are people already wanting to invade the pitch. Surely this wins the series for West Indies? Full toss, on off, Taylor wants to hit it for a six over leg, gets a thick edge that is skied to Sammy at point
full, on off, dug out for a single
full, on off, will get just the single
full, on leg, driven to long-on for one
Best won't get five, but he has sealed the match for sure. length ball outside off, Boult is not keen to get in line as it is bowled at 144ks. Beaten
full, on off, driven down the ground, turns down the single
full, angling in, beats the huge swing. Beaten

West Indies have won their first ODI series against a side other than Bangladesh or Zimbabwe in more than four years. Slower ball, beats the bat, and the keeper completes the run-put after the New Zealand Nos 10 and 11 are confused and both in the middle of the pitch
